ackground:#ffc;\"\n| 9 November 2014\u2013<br>16 November 2014 || [[2014 ATP World Tour Finals|ATP World Tour Finals]] || [[London]] || [[ATP World Tour Finals]] || Hard (i) || DNS || 0 || 200 || style=\"background:#afeeee;\"| Did not advance from the group stage\n|}\n\n==Yearly records==\n\n===Head-to-head matchups===\n''Ordered by number of wins''\n<small>('''Bold''' denotes a top 10 player at the time of match, ''Italic'' means top 50)</small>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-4}}\n* ''{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Feliciano L\u00f3pez]]'' 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|POR}} ''[[Jo\u00e3o Sousa]]'' 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|POL}} ''[[Jerzy Janowicz]]'' 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|AUT}} [[J\u00fcrgen Melzer]] 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|RSA}} ''[[Kevin Anderson (tennis)|Kevin Anderson]]'' 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} ''[[Tommy Robredo]]'' 2\u20130\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} '''''[[Jo-Wilfried Tsonga]]''''' 2\u20131{{#tag:ref|Tsonga was ranked in the top 50 for their first two meetings (1\u20131) but top 10 for their third (1\u20130).|name=\"note1\"|group=\"nb\"}}\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} '''[[David Ferrer]]''' 2\u20131\n* {{flagicon|QAT}} [[Mousa Shanan Zayed]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Go Soeda]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Vincent Millot]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[St\u00e9phane Robert]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|USA}} [[Donald Young (tennis)|Donald Young]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|USA}} ''[[Sam Querrey]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} ''[[\u00c9douard Roger-Vasselin]]'' 1\u20130\n\n{{col-4}}\n* {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Dominic Thiem]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} ''[[Pablo And\u00fajar]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} ''[[Gilles Simon]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|CZE}} ''[[Luk\u00e1\u0161 Rosol]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Ji\u0159\u00ed Vesel\u00fd]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Matthew Ebden]] 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|ITA}} ''[[Andreas Seppi]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} ''[[Nicolas Almagro]] '' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} ''[[Marcel Granollers]]'' 1\u20130\n* {{flagicon|KAZ}} [[Andrey Golubev]] 1\u2013